<span id="freeTextContainer627660694264780122">Mishima&apos;s genius isn&apos;t just the art of the Japanese language or his vast knowledge of Greek myths, arts, and literature of the world. He had such an understanding of human nature and created characters that behaved in the darkest way possible. Also, I had never read a child-birth scene as intense as it was in this novel. It was grotesque and bloody but utterly magnificent at the same time. </span>
