<div id="review_15312178" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/15312178" />
    <a title="Louis" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/801827-louis"><img alt="Louis" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1200788043p2/801827.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/15312178?book_show_action=true">Feb 13, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Louis" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Louis" href="/user/show/801827-louis">Louis</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Japanophiles, homophiles, misanthropes and general bibliophiles.</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Louis by: </span>
      Geoffrey
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/801827-louis?shelf=japanese">japanese</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer15312178" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16297587173794312700">The amount of time it took me to read this book is by no means a testament to my opinion of it. I am in love with this book. Like most of my favourites it says something about the nature of relationships and, although the actions of the main characters are cruel they are somehow believable. A mark of good writing is to take something difficult to believe (like such blatant misogyny) and make it not only believable but understandable. While some Feminists-with-a-capital-F might find the revenge p</span>
  <span id="freeText16297587173794312700" style="display:none">The amount of time it took me to read this book is by no means a testament to my opinion of it. I am in love with this book. Like most of my favourites it says something about the nature of relationships and, although the actions of the main characters are cruel they are somehow believable. A mark of good writing is to take something difficult to believe (like such blatant misogyny) and make it not only believable but understandable. While some Feminists-with-a-capital-F might find the revenge plans of an old man who sees himself scorned by women, and decides to exact his revenge, as a little sexist, that would be essentially missing the point. I can't decide whether I love this book because or despite the absurd misogyny. It makes me want to revive my long shelved plans for a PhD. Not on this book, but on topics dealt with therein.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16297587173794312700" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


